        THE STRAITS TIMES B6 THURSDAY, JULY 16, 2020 | | | Save The Date The latest happenings and events you won’t want to miss TOP PICKS Make USA Rice the option for your daily choice For Asian meals United States-cultivated Okome premium short grain rice is perfect for any Asian household. Because of its sweet flavour, and soft and sticky texture when cooked, it is perfect for Japanese, Korean and Taiwanese dishes. Available in 1kg and 4.5kg variants at major supermarke­ts and online grocer y stores.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Singapore Gifts & Premiums Fair,                                                                    Sphere Exhibits, a wholly-owned subsidiar y of Singapore Press Holdings, is taking its threein-one trade show for corporate gifts and office, printing, packaging, signage and labelling solutions to the digital space.
Singapore Gifts & Premiums Fair (SGPFair), Office Expo Asia (OEA) and PrintPack+Sign (PP+S) are slated to be held virtually this year due to the large-scale event restrictio­ns to curb the spread of Covid-19. They will feature products and talks to address the branding and marketing needs of businesses.
Explore SGPFair if you’re searching for the finest names in promotiona­l, corporate, incentive and retail gifts. OEA will enable attendees to meet industry players and thought leaders in the workplace solutions and developmen­t industr y, as well as highlight office products and stationer y supplies. Businesses looking for the best in print and packaging innovation, signage and labelling technologi­es, trends and designs should mark their calendars for the PP+S event.
Attendees can also gain access to live webinars about branding, marketing and personal developmen­t. Exclusive deals and discounts will also be available, as well as a lucky draw event. Admission to the three-day show is free. Open for trade and corporate visitors only. Visit the following websites for registrati­on and more informatio­n: Chewy rice Short grain rice has a plump, almost round kernel. When cooked, it becomes soft and chewy, firm to the bite. Short grain rice is a good choice for dishes with a creamy consistenc­y. Available in white, brown, red and black variants. Apart from helping businesses discover options for their corporate needs, Sphere Exhibits sees the three-day live vir tual exhibition as a venue for exhibitors to promote their products and ser vices, drive leads and generate revenue.
Attendees will be able to text and video chat with the exhibitors during the show dates. The virtual event will be accessible to all attendees until Nov 30. Aug 20, Health Fiesta 2020 Nutrient-rich varieties Here are some health gadgets that will be featured in this virtual event by Sphere Exhibits.                                                                                  USA Rice packs a nutritiona­l punch. They provide more than 15 essential vitamins and minerals, including folic acid, B vitamins, potassium, magnesium, selenium, fibre, iron and zinc. They are also produced sustainabl­y and are naturally free from sodium, cholestero­l, gluten and GMO. Quick pulse check Stylish hearing aid Easy contact tracing The Fingertip Pulse Oximeter from healthcare solutions retailer OWELL is a helpful tool to have at home. The product measures your pulse rate and arterial oxygen saturation (haemoglobi­n oxygenatio­n), which are two important indicators of one’s respirator y function. The Fingertip Pulse Oximeter is equipped with a pulse strength indicator and low oxygen level alert, with readings displayed within 10 seconds. The product is lightweigh­t, compact and suitable for profession­al use as well. Call 6339-0613 or visit www.owellbodyc­are.com to place an order. Virto Marvel Black is a custom-made hearing aid that looks like a wireless earbud from The Hearing Specialist Group. Developed by Swiss brand Phonak, this in-the-canal hearing aid can help you hear better during video calls and crowded places as it can be connected to your phone, TV, tablet and computer. You can sign up for a compliment­ary one-to-one consultati­on and a hearing aid experience session with The Hearing Specialist Group’s audiologis­ts. Visit www. thehearing­specialist.com.sg, call 6346-0858 or WhatsApp 9634-2369 for more details. Artificial intelligen­ce and smart product solutions provider Variantz is offering a contactles­s facial recognitio­n product for commercial use, deemed useful for contact tracing in the nation’s fight against Covid-19. The Variantz Vantage HLS can identify individual­s while measuring their temperatur­e, and detect if they are wearing a face mask. It is CE-certified, ISO-compliant and comes with a cloud applicatio­n for security management. Visit www.variantz.com/ product-page/vantage-hls-c or e-mail covid19@ variantz.com to find out more. No supply shortage Because the United States can produce all types of rice — be it long, medium or short grain — Singaporea­ns can expect these imported varieties on the shelves of leading supermarke­ts. In par ticular, be on the look out for basmati, brown, calrose, glutinous and wild rice. They are available in grocer y stores islandwide. PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW
